<h4 id="1-2-4-captions-live-aa"><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/media-equiv-real-time-captions.html">1.2.4 Captions (live) (AA)</a></h4>
<p>Live broadcast video must have captions that are synchronised with the audio content of the video. This ensures that the information communicated by the audio part of the video is available to people who cannot hear it.</p>
<h5 id="requirements-what-to-do">Requirements / What to do?</h5>

<ul>
<li>  All live video content has captions that are synchronised with the audio content of the video.</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="common-mistakes">Common mistakes</h5>

<ul>
<li>  The live video does not have synchronised captions;</li>
<li>  The live video has captions but they are not synchronised with the audio content of the video.</li>
</ul>
